WEBVTT

00:01.126 --> 00:02.753
PETER: <i>Previously on</i> White Collar...

00:03.003 --> 00:04.922
The Burkes are going to Washington.

00:05.005 --> 00:06.006
(GASPS)

00:06.298 --> 00:07.549
-(PANTING)
-Good. Here it comes.

00:08.008 --> 00:09.009
(BABY GURGLING)

00:09.092 --> 00:10.177
NEAL: The <i>Mosconi Codex.</i>

00:10.260 --> 00:12.846
If this book is a puzzle,
maybe these are the pieces.

00:12.930 --> 00:14.264
Take a look at the pages.

00:14.348 --> 00:15.599
<i>-Rain Man</i> it.
-MOZZIE: I got it.

00:15.682 --> 00:17.309
This is the idol of Sita.

00:17.392 --> 00:19.269
The idol had eyes
made out of rare diamonds.

00:19.353 --> 00:21.522
The Hope Diamond.
We're looking for its twin.

00:21.605 --> 00:24.858
PETER: This is Rebecca's apartment.
Who is she, Neal?

00:24.942 --> 00:27.110
PETER: Her real name is Rachel Turner.

00:27.194 --> 00:29.112
MI5. She was one of their agents.

00:29.196 --> 00:30.614
<i>The prime suspect in the murders</i>

00:30.697 --> 00:32.824
<i>of Curtis Hagen and Agent David Siegel.</i>

00:32.908 --> 00:34.785
JONES: We have full video
of her apartment.

00:34.868 --> 00:36.411
PETER: Neal, she's in love with you.

00:39.206 --> 00:41.041
You are under arrest for murder.

00:41.542 --> 00:43.877
AUTOMATED VOICE: <i>Do you accept</i>
<i>a collect call from inmate...</i>

00:43.961 --> 00:44.962
REBECCA: <i>Rachel Turner.</i>

00:45.045 --> 00:46.213
I'll see you soon.

00:49.967 --> 00:52.469
NEAL: You know D.C. was built
on a swamp, right?

00:52.553 --> 00:54.304
PETER: Total myth. It was all wetlands.

00:54.388 --> 00:58.350
That's a distinction without a difference.
Pack a mosquito net.

00:58.433 --> 00:59.434
I'm from upstate.

00:59.518 --> 01:02.521
Our mosquitoes resemble small buzzards.
I'll be fine.

01:02.729 --> 01:04.439
That experience with bloodsuckers

01:04.523 --> 01:07.401
will come in handy when you start
rubbing elbows with congressmen.

01:07.484 --> 01:10.737
Well, thankfully, politics is only part
of my new job.

01:11.822 --> 01:14.241
Gosh, you know, these last few months
have been...

01:14.324 --> 01:15.492
"Insane" will do.

01:15.617 --> 01:16.869
Yeah.

01:16.952 --> 01:18.662
Look, Rebecca deceived us all.

01:18.745 --> 01:20.414
Are you holding up okay?

01:20.998 --> 01:22.332
Rebecca's behind me.

01:22.416 --> 01:25.127
Right now I'd rather focus
on what my future looks like.

01:25.294 --> 01:26.920
Good, which is why I've been giving

01:27.004 --> 01:29.381
a lot of thought as to who
your next handler will be.

01:29.464 --> 01:31.425
That's not the future I have in mind.

01:32.009 --> 01:33.135
The promotion at D.C...

01:33.218 --> 01:36.471
Your case history was a huge factor
in that decision, right?

01:36.722 --> 01:37.806
That's right.

01:37.890 --> 01:39.975
It was based in part on my successes
as a field agent.

01:40.058 --> 01:41.560
Our successes.

01:41.894 --> 01:44.813
No more handlers,
no more cases, no more anklet.

01:45.230 --> 01:46.356
Neal, what are you saying?

01:46.440 --> 01:48.525
I'm saying I want my sentence
to be dropped.

01:49.610 --> 01:52.988
I've talked to a lawyer.
A recommendation from you is critical.

02:03.290 --> 02:05.501
Neal, you have time to serve.

02:05.584 --> 02:08.170
Being ASAC doesn't mean
I give you special treatment.

02:08.253 --> 02:09.713
It has nothing to do with rank.

02:09.796 --> 02:11.924
It's because
you're my supervising officer.

02:12.174 --> 02:14.176
I'm asking you to do what's right.

02:14.259 --> 02:15.969
Oh, I have spent a lot of my time with you

02:16.053 --> 02:17.679
thinking about what's right.

02:17.930 --> 02:21.391
And what I've learned is that
there's never a simple answer.

02:21.475 --> 02:24.311
Hey, I just got off the phone
with the prosecutor's office.

02:24.436 --> 02:26.355
You know the print on the bullet
inside Rebecca's gun?

02:26.438 --> 02:27.814
They're moving to indict?

02:27.898 --> 02:29.566
Yeah, first thing tomorrow morning.

02:30.317 --> 02:32.361
(EXHALES) It's over, Neal.

02:32.778 --> 02:34.988
Yeah, it's over.

02:36.490 --> 02:39.284
Listen, they want the evidence boxed up
and shipped immediately.

02:39.368 --> 02:41.328
You want me to round up
a couple of probies?

02:42.079 --> 02:44.706
You know, on my very first case,

02:44.790 --> 02:47.626
Hughes had me bag and tag
all the evidence myself.

02:47.709 --> 02:50.379
It's only fitting
that I do it on my last case.

02:50.963 --> 02:53.173
Come on, Neal, let's box it all up.

02:57.010 --> 02:58.053
All of it?

02:58.345 --> 02:59.346
All of it.

03:10.649 --> 03:11.650
(EXHALES)

03:25.831 --> 03:27.624
-Ready, Neal?
-Yes.

03:49.605 --> 03:51.231
-Beers at work?
-Yeah.

03:51.315 --> 03:52.983
I know you're a stickler for rules,

03:53.066 --> 03:55.694
but if ever there was
a time to break one, it's now.

03:55.777 --> 03:58.530
Besides, we are officially off the clock.

04:00.490 --> 04:01.742
(CELL PHONE BUZZING)

04:01.825 --> 04:03.035
PETER: Mmm.

04:04.494 --> 04:05.537
That yours?

04:05.621 --> 04:07.122
-No, I thought it was yours.
-No.

04:28.685 --> 04:30.187
It's one of Rebecca's burner phones.

04:30.270 --> 04:32.773
Her voice mail access
will be password protected.

04:33.106 --> 04:35.275
The tech guys unlocked all her phones.

04:35.359 --> 04:36.818
It should be as simple as...

04:37.027 --> 04:39.863
MAN: <i>Rebecca Lowe, I got this number</i>
<i>from one of your associates.</i>

04:39.947 --> 04:43.158
<i>I'm in need of your services immediately.</i>

04:43.242 --> 04:44.660
<i>Call me back.</i>

04:44.743 --> 04:46.954
We need to see where this leads.

04:47.037 --> 04:49.456
If Rebecca's other clients
are anything like Hagen...

04:49.540 --> 04:50.624
Someone could end up dead.

04:51.375 --> 04:53.794
The caller got her name
and number secondhand.

04:53.877 --> 04:56.296
We could send someone
undercover to meet him.

04:56.380 --> 04:58.549
If he knows what she looks like,
he'll bolt.

04:58.799 --> 05:00.467
-But if he doesn't...
-We have a case.

05:00.884 --> 05:03.679
Now, normally, I'd send you in undercover
for something like this.

05:03.762 --> 05:04.930
This isn't <i>Some Like It Hot.</i>

05:05.013 --> 05:06.557
You have someone good in mind?

05:06.640 --> 05:08.892
Yeah, one of the best agents I know.

05:09.184 --> 05:11.436
Smart, relentless, tough.

05:11.520 --> 05:13.897
Able to leap tall buildings
in a single bound?

05:13.981 --> 05:15.399
Wouldn't be surprised.

05:15.774 --> 05:16.942
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

05:18.277 --> 05:19.611
Hey, boss.

05:21.154 --> 05:22.489
Let's get to work.

05:27.452 --> 05:29.496
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

05:48.974 --> 05:52.019
So let me get this straight.
After we find out the client's identity,

05:52.102 --> 05:54.771
I have to impersonate Rebecca,
who's really Rachel,

05:54.855 --> 05:56.690
hoping he doesn't know that
she isn't a biracial woman

05:56.773 --> 05:58.358
who has to pump every three hours?

05:58.442 --> 06:00.527
-Pump?
-I'm a fantastic multitasker.

06:00.611 --> 06:02.070
I'll do it on the fly.

06:02.154 --> 06:04.907
Then I determine what the job is,
pretend to carry it out,

06:04.990 --> 06:07.659
and deliver evidence of
completion to our mystery man,

06:07.743 --> 06:09.828
which, given Rebecca's history,
might include murder.

06:09.912 --> 06:11.205
Yeah.

06:11.330 --> 06:14.875
Look, Diana, truth is, who knows
if we even have a case?

06:14.958 --> 06:17.336
You know, I just wanted
to bring you up to speed.

06:17.419 --> 06:19.963
Tons of unknowns,
and I'm not sure if we'll pursue it.

06:20.380 --> 06:21.673
Peter, I'm in.

06:22.090 --> 06:25.719
A bad guy wants to hire a bad girl
to do some really bad stuff.

06:25.802 --> 06:27.930
I'm the best person in the division
to keep that from happening.

06:28.013 --> 06:30.057
-You know that.
-I do.

06:30.140 --> 06:31.183
Good.

06:31.266 --> 06:33.852
Now, I got to go change, and so does he.

06:36.230 --> 06:38.649
You know your way
around a dirty diaper, right?

06:55.541 --> 06:57.292
Neal, the damn <i>Codex.</i>

06:57.376 --> 06:58.877
You have any idea what happens

06:58.961 --> 07:01.296
when you commit
something like that to memory?

07:01.380 --> 07:02.506
It haunts you.

07:02.589 --> 07:05.259
Exactly! Try to sleep... <i>Codex.</i>

07:05.342 --> 07:07.469
Sit down to a delicious bowl of muesli...

07:07.553 --> 07:08.804
<i>Codex.</i>

07:08.887 --> 07:11.515
All these signs and symbols
floating around in my head,

07:11.598 --> 07:15.519
combining, separating,
recombining, mocking me.

07:15.602 --> 07:16.728
Relax.

07:16.812 --> 07:18.230
Now that Rebecca is gone,

07:18.313 --> 07:20.607
we can take a breath
and go at this the right way.

07:20.691 --> 07:21.775
Think about it.

07:21.859 --> 07:24.236
Nobody is looking
for the diamond except us.

07:24.945 --> 07:26.280
You're right.

07:26.780 --> 07:27.865
This could be it.

07:27.948 --> 07:31.201
Everything we've always dreamed about.
It's within reach.

07:31.285 --> 07:35.080
With the money from the diamond,
we could build a small consortium,

07:35.163 --> 07:39.084
a network of associates,
properly financed cons.

07:39.168 --> 07:41.086
Maybe even a few small drones.

07:41.336 --> 07:43.589
Drones? I see you've
really thought this through.

07:43.672 --> 07:44.798
It's perfect.

07:44.882 --> 07:47.050
An illegitimate empire

07:47.134 --> 07:51.388
paid for with the legitimate proceeds
from the diamond.

07:51.471 --> 07:53.473
Neal, it's our cotillion.

07:53.640 --> 07:55.225
(CELL PHONE CHIMING)

07:57.436 --> 07:59.521
That's Peter. I got to run.

08:00.522 --> 08:02.858
We're tracking someone
who contacted Rebecca

08:02.941 --> 08:04.151
about doing a job.

08:04.735 --> 08:07.279
Diana's coming off maternity
leave to go undercover.

08:08.113 --> 08:10.032
What will she do with Teddy?

08:10.115 --> 08:11.116
You mean Theo?

08:11.617 --> 08:14.369
Well, like most women
from Gloria Steinem on,

08:14.453 --> 08:16.038
she'll probably hire a babysitter.

08:16.121 --> 08:18.582
I've never even met my namesake,

08:18.665 --> 08:22.836
yet some stranger is gonna mold
his young, pliable mind?

08:23.086 --> 08:25.172
I delivered that child, Neal.

08:25.255 --> 08:27.674
How about we channel
that righteous indignation

08:27.758 --> 08:29.051
into finding the diamond?

08:31.428 --> 08:32.638
(SIGHS)

08:44.066 --> 08:45.567
Welcome back, Agent Berrigan.

08:45.651 --> 08:47.694
Thank you, Agent Jones.

08:48.278 --> 08:49.530
Now...

08:51.281 --> 08:52.533
What do we know about this guy?

08:52.616 --> 08:55.702
Nothing. We've got
a short voice mail and a phone.

08:55.827 --> 08:57.746
Yeah, no ID, no location.

08:58.121 --> 09:00.624
Whoever he is, if he doesn't
hear back from Rebecca Lowe,

09:00.707 --> 09:02.251
he'll find someone else for the job.

09:02.334 --> 09:03.919
-We can't let that happen.
-NEAL: I agree.

09:04.002 --> 09:05.671
If this is all we've got, let's use it.

09:06.505 --> 09:08.674
(DIALING)

09:09.883 --> 09:11.218
(RINGING ON LINE)

09:14.721 --> 09:16.223
MAN: <i>I was hoping you'd call sooner.</i>

09:17.349 --> 09:19.560
I call when I call. What's the assignment?

09:19.893 --> 09:22.813
<i>All pertinent information will be left</i>
<i>at a drop site this afternoon.</i>

09:23.522 --> 09:24.565
Negative.

09:26.567 --> 09:28.610
<i>I was given to understand</i>
<i>this is how you did things.</i>

09:28.694 --> 09:31.822
Then you understood wrong.
We meet in person in public.

09:31.905 --> 09:34.074
Those are my rules.
If you don't like them, too bad.

09:36.493 --> 09:37.786
<i>Fine.</i>

09:37.870 --> 09:39.788
<i>Crawford Plaza, tomorrow at noon.</i>

09:40.038 --> 09:42.291
<i>My associate briefed me on your signal.</i>

09:42.374 --> 09:43.542
<i>I'll be looking for it.</i>

09:48.922 --> 09:51.550
Any bright ideas on what
Rebecca's signal could be?

09:53.218 --> 09:54.636
There's one way to find out.

10:15.866 --> 10:19.870
She may not have much to say, Neal,
not to me.

10:19.953 --> 10:21.747
Well, I'm sure you have ways
of getting her to talk.

10:21.830 --> 10:23.457
Are you in contact with the van?

10:23.540 --> 10:26.293
Up and running. I'll try to make it fast.

10:46.813 --> 10:48.398
Agent Burke.

10:49.191 --> 10:51.985
I never thought I'd actually look forward
to a trip to the FBI.

10:53.362 --> 10:55.614
Didn't feel like coming down
to the correction center?

10:55.989 --> 10:58.534
Don't like seeing what happens
to the stuff you flush down the drain?

10:58.617 --> 11:02.371
I like to control my environment,
which makes two of us.

11:04.915 --> 11:06.333
I could have killed you, you know.

11:07.251 --> 11:09.753
I had you in my sights several times.

11:10.045 --> 11:12.548
But I never would have done that to Neal.
It would have torn him up.

11:15.843 --> 11:16.969
<i>Why am I here?</i>

11:17.469 --> 11:18.846
To strike a deal.

11:19.471 --> 11:21.306
Don't suppose
you could help me with these.

11:22.266 --> 11:25.143
Your cell right now.
I hear it's pretty grim.

11:25.644 --> 11:28.272
I can talk to the warden
about getting you some southern exposure.

11:28.355 --> 11:29.356
Not interested.

11:30.232 --> 11:32.651
An extra hour or two
in the yard every day?

11:33.318 --> 11:35.028
You know I only want one thing.

11:36.405 --> 11:38.949
But what is it that you want?

11:40.492 --> 11:44.121
I want to know the signal you use
when first making contact with a client.

11:44.204 --> 11:48.041
Hmm. Just to quench your curiosity?
Something to put in the scrapbook?

11:48.792 --> 11:52.379
Or did I get a job? Hmm!

11:53.130 --> 11:54.715
It's good to feel wanted.

11:54.798 --> 11:56.550
Your signal. What is it?

11:56.633 --> 11:57.759
I'm not telling you.

11:58.302 --> 11:59.720
<i>But I will tell Neal,</i>

11:59.970 --> 12:02.556
<i>after I've had a chance to talk to him</i>
<i>about a few things.</i>

12:03.473 --> 12:04.975
(SIGHS)

12:06.935 --> 12:08.270
No can do.

12:08.729 --> 12:11.440
I'm sure glad I didn't waste
a drive down to the MCC.

12:11.940 --> 12:14.318
Enjoy your view
of civilization while you can.

12:15.068 --> 12:16.445
Okay.

12:19.031 --> 12:20.699
Okay, I will tell you.

12:21.283 --> 12:23.744
But then I want to see him.

12:24.578 --> 12:26.163
Those are my terms.

12:27.789 --> 12:29.291
How's that sound, Neal?

12:32.127 --> 12:33.295
(TAPPING ON GLASS)

12:36.256 --> 12:37.716
PETER: <i>Looks like we have a deal.</i>

12:41.803 --> 12:44.264
The signal is a watch,
worn on the left hand,

12:44.348 --> 12:45.891
banded upside down.

12:46.433 --> 12:47.809
What time?

12:48.936 --> 12:50.896
It should be set to 10:20.

12:52.439 --> 12:53.815
Happy?

12:54.316 --> 12:57.319
That you'll soon be serving
two consecutive life sentences?

12:57.402 --> 12:59.321
Yeah, I'm ecstatic.

13:01.156 --> 13:03.492
I gave you what you wanted.

13:05.035 --> 13:06.578
Now it's my turn.

13:21.635 --> 13:24.221
PETER: You're not going in
until we know the signal works.

13:24.304 --> 13:25.931
And if it does...

13:27.057 --> 13:30.519
Just in case I need to be
in contact with you.

13:30.644 --> 13:31.728
You sure you're up for this?

13:32.563 --> 13:35.274
I wish I could say
absence made the heart grow fonder.

13:36.149 --> 13:37.734
Jones, how we looking?

13:38.151 --> 13:39.945
We've got eyes and ears on Diana.

13:40.153 --> 13:42.698
-Diana, you with us?
-DIANA: <i>Copy that.</i>

13:50.622 --> 13:53.041
It looks like somebody's approaching.
Here we go.

13:59.214 --> 14:00.549
Lovely day.

14:06.805 --> 14:07.890
I like your watch.

14:08.682 --> 14:10.601
You want something taken care of?

14:10.976 --> 14:12.769
You tell me what you want me to do.

14:12.853 --> 14:14.104
I do it, you pay.

14:14.479 --> 14:15.689
That's the deal.

14:16.064 --> 14:18.775
I don't discuss the job
till we're safely indoors.

14:18.859 --> 14:20.861
Given my line of work,
you can't be too careful.

14:32.915 --> 14:34.416
(CAMERA CLICKING)

14:34.958 --> 14:37.711
Peter, we've got a hitch.
Diana's following our suspect.

14:37.794 --> 14:39.963
-No clue where they're headed.
<i>-Did you ID him yet?</i>

14:44.551 --> 14:46.261
Yeah. Conrad Worth.

14:46.345 --> 14:49.640
He was a suspect in an S.E.C.
investigation a few months back.

14:50.390 --> 14:51.683
Never did pin anything on him,

14:51.767 --> 14:53.602
but he's looking really shady
right about now.

14:54.603 --> 14:56.688
Peter, I don't like this.

14:56.772 --> 14:58.273
<i>Someone backing her up?</i>

14:58.357 --> 15:00.234
Yep, I am.

15:01.568 --> 15:04.279
Diana called an audible.
She's following the suspect.

15:05.239 --> 15:06.823
Make it quick in there.

15:21.839 --> 15:23.215
Neal.

15:24.216 --> 15:26.677
I hate for you to see me like this.

15:30.472 --> 15:32.808
Do you remember what
my last words to you were?

15:34.810 --> 15:36.061
"I'll see you soon."

15:37.354 --> 15:38.605
Here you are.

15:39.106 --> 15:40.732
It's like something out of a novel.

15:40.816 --> 15:45.070
Yeah, the kind you buy in an airport
and then leave in your seat-back pocket.

15:45.153 --> 15:48.156
Come on, I'm still me.

15:48.991 --> 15:50.742
I'm still Rebecca.

15:50.993 --> 15:52.327
Don't you see that?

15:52.661 --> 15:54.037
When I first met you,

15:54.121 --> 15:57.207
what I saw was the innocence of Kate,

15:57.457 --> 15:59.710
the wit of Sara, the allure of Alex.

15:59.793 --> 16:02.629
Exactly. I'm the perfect woman for you.

16:02.713 --> 16:05.299
No, you made yourself into that,

16:05.382 --> 16:09.261
into something you're not 'cause that's
the job you were hired to do.

16:10.095 --> 16:12.890
What you are is a murderer.

16:14.099 --> 16:16.476
You can't separate the woman
you fell in love with

16:16.560 --> 16:18.437
from any of my identities.

16:18.979 --> 16:21.148
It turned real.

16:21.857 --> 16:24.276
You saw the true me.

16:24.860 --> 16:26.445
And I know you.

16:27.237 --> 16:29.406
I can tell you still have feelings for me.

16:31.950 --> 16:34.494
Rebecca, Rachel,

16:34.620 --> 16:36.246
and whatever name
you decide to call yourself

16:36.330 --> 16:38.582
in the cafeteria line...

16:39.416 --> 16:40.667
It's over.

16:43.337 --> 16:45.881
See, I can see what you're doing.

16:45.964 --> 16:48.008
That slick facade.

16:48.091 --> 16:50.677
It means you feel threatened.

16:50.761 --> 16:54.348
Neal, I can see
right through all your lies.

17:00.270 --> 17:02.147
I admire the minimalist touch.

17:02.231 --> 17:03.565
We just moved in.

17:03.649 --> 17:06.610
My partners and I,
we come and go as we please.

17:06.693 --> 17:11.114
And besides, this day and age,
what more do you need?

17:16.995 --> 17:18.539
It's lovely.

17:18.622 --> 17:20.791
Now, can we get down to specifics?

17:20.916 --> 17:22.042
It's funny.

17:22.125 --> 17:23.293
With all I've heard about you,

17:23.377 --> 17:26.171
I was expecting someone different.

17:29.383 --> 17:31.134
Please, sit down.

17:32.678 --> 17:34.012
Talk to me, Jones.

17:45.816 --> 17:47.526
I've got eyes on Diana.

17:48.026 --> 17:49.486
They're on his terrace.

17:49.987 --> 17:52.155
First sign of trouble, I'm in.

17:54.533 --> 17:56.952
You're not the only job on my horizon.

17:57.035 --> 17:59.413
Please tell me I'm not wasting my time.

18:01.832 --> 18:04.418
When I first heard about you,
it was only in whispers.

18:04.501 --> 18:06.962
Your exploits are the stuff of legend.

18:07.504 --> 18:08.797
There was one story.

18:08.881 --> 18:10.048
You couldn't forget it if you've heard it.

18:10.132 --> 18:12.551
Some friends of mine,
they saw it with their own eyes.

18:13.343 --> 18:16.889
Caracas, May 2009,

18:17.181 --> 18:18.348
remind me.

18:19.057 --> 18:20.601
How did that go down?

18:21.185 --> 18:22.895
Enough with the closure, Neal.

18:23.353 --> 18:25.397
I need you to ask about...

18:27.900 --> 18:30.485
Caracas, May 2009.

18:31.028 --> 18:32.321
I want to know what happened.

18:32.404 --> 18:34.615
Neal, are you helping Agent Burke

18:34.698 --> 18:37.492
make sure some bumbling agent
is safely vetted?

18:37.618 --> 18:39.745
That's so beneath you. Come on.

18:42.831 --> 18:44.333
Then I guess we're
out of things to talk about.

18:44.416 --> 18:45.667
All right.

18:46.251 --> 18:48.837
You want to know some things?
I got some questions, too.

18:50.047 --> 18:52.799
One for one,
we answer each other truthfully.

18:52.883 --> 18:54.760
-Okay.
-But if you lie to me,

18:54.843 --> 18:56.345
I lie to you.

18:56.553 --> 19:00.807
And besides, lovers are experts
at sniffing out one another's deceptions.

19:03.560 --> 19:05.312
You know, what you're
asking me to admit to

19:05.395 --> 19:06.855
could get me thrown in jail.

19:06.939 --> 19:08.232
Are you wearing a wire?

19:08.649 --> 19:09.816
Please.

19:09.900 --> 19:11.443
Then let me be blunt.

19:11.777 --> 19:13.612
I don't discuss past jobs.

19:14.738 --> 19:16.073
Well, let me be blunt.

19:16.156 --> 19:18.158
I'm not sure you are who you say you are,

19:18.242 --> 19:19.785
so tell me what I need to know.

19:22.788 --> 19:24.039
The story, Neal.

19:24.456 --> 19:25.791
<i>We're running out of time.</i>

19:25.874 --> 19:27.251
REBECCA: How about I go first?

19:27.334 --> 19:29.294
Something light to warm us up?

19:29.378 --> 19:30.754
(NEAL CLEARS THROAT)

19:31.797 --> 19:33.715
Do you think you're smarter

19:33.799 --> 19:35.384
than your old friend Peter Burke?

19:35.467 --> 19:36.635
Yes.

19:36.969 --> 19:38.679
<i>And Peter thinks he's smarter than me.</i>

19:39.054 --> 19:40.430
Well, you can't both be right.

19:40.514 --> 19:42.266
Which has resulted in years of debate.

19:42.349 --> 19:43.767
Now, one for one, truth for truth.

19:43.851 --> 19:45.143
Tell me what happened in Caracas.

19:50.732 --> 19:53.026
May 21st, 2009.

19:53.110 --> 19:56.446
An opera at the Teatro Teresa CarreÃ±o.

19:56.530 --> 19:57.865
Tight security.

19:58.532 --> 20:00.367
I snuck in, removed a wire

20:00.450 --> 20:02.661
from the orchestra's piano,
and slipped it...

20:02.744 --> 20:06.748
Over the lead actor's neck
as the first act was ending.

20:06.957 --> 20:09.001
He owed a very large debt
to the city's mayor

20:09.084 --> 20:10.252
and refused to pay,

20:10.335 --> 20:13.672
so I left his body onstage
and his head on the mayor's doorstep.

20:14.006 --> 20:15.507
That's the short version.

20:15.591 --> 20:18.927
I left out the '54 Gullwing
and the bridge jump over the Guaire.

20:22.389 --> 20:25.309
It's nice to finally hear it
from the source.

20:28.103 --> 20:30.814
This is the address
of an R & D facility in midtown.

20:30.898 --> 20:34.026
I need what's in vault 23, compartment 3.

20:34.234 --> 20:37.029
The haul is tiny,
but its importance to me is not.

20:37.529 --> 20:38.697
And what is it?

20:38.780 --> 20:40.032
It's a thumb drive.

20:40.157 --> 20:42.618
I need it Friday morning,
9:00 a.m., period.

20:42.701 --> 20:45.204
I expect my compensation upon delivery.

20:46.496 --> 20:49.208
See, this R & D facility, it's not like
slipping into an opera house.

20:49.291 --> 20:50.834
It's incredibly secure.

20:51.335 --> 20:54.421
I mean, maybe we should bring
along some, I don't know,

20:54.505 --> 20:56.215
muscle in case you get into trouble.

20:57.049 --> 20:58.300
(GROANING)

20:58.383 --> 21:00.469
One thing I forgot
to tell you about Caracas.

21:00.886 --> 21:03.514
Someone got in my way as
I was leaving the opera house.

21:03.597 --> 21:06.475
So I snapped the tendon
in his middle finger.

21:06.558 --> 21:08.852
Tendons are elastic, like rubber bands.

21:09.353 --> 21:12.940
I later heard his doctor had to fish
for the severed end deep inside his elbow.

21:13.440 --> 21:15.025
That enough muscle for you?

21:16.401 --> 21:18.153
You'll have the drive by Friday morning.

21:23.909 --> 21:25.452
Not a bad story, huh?

21:25.744 --> 21:28.413
What's your professional opinion,
one thief to another?

21:30.165 --> 21:31.500
You're not a thief.

21:32.835 --> 21:34.878
Admit it, you still love me.

21:35.587 --> 21:37.631
I wouldn't call what we had love.

21:37.714 --> 21:39.091
I disagree.

21:39.925 --> 21:41.343
Neal...

21:41.927 --> 21:44.596
You and I belong together.

21:44.680 --> 21:49.810
Uh-huh. And how would that work exactly,
conjugal visits every third Thursday?

21:49.893 --> 21:51.103
(CHUCKLES)

21:51.186 --> 21:52.813
Circumstances change.

21:54.273 --> 21:56.191
Come on, four years ago,
would you have guessed

21:56.275 --> 21:57.651
that you'd be a snitch

21:57.734 --> 21:59.570
for the very people
that were hunting you down?

22:03.490 --> 22:05.450
That's it, Neal. We're done.

22:08.620 --> 22:11.623
So, you going after the diamond?

22:12.374 --> 22:13.750
Who says I don't already have it?

22:13.834 --> 22:15.002
I do.

22:15.085 --> 22:17.629
That little thing you just did
with your eyebrow, it's a tell.

22:21.758 --> 22:23.385
Maybe I'm working on it.

22:24.344 --> 22:26.847
Or maybe the diamond doesn't even exist.

22:26.930 --> 22:28.473
Oh, it exists.

22:30.017 --> 22:32.603
And you're getting close.

22:33.520 --> 22:36.356
What are you gonna do if you find it
with that thing on your ankle?

22:36.440 --> 22:37.524
What then?

22:39.860 --> 22:40.986
I don't know.

22:44.489 --> 22:48.243
But I do know that whatever happens next
sure as hell doesn't include you.

22:50.954 --> 22:52.247
Good-bye, Rebecca.

23:14.645 --> 23:16.980
I think you invented a new sport in there.

23:17.356 --> 23:18.899
Psychological judo.

23:19.942 --> 23:22.402
Well, they say throwing salt on the wound

23:22.486 --> 23:23.904
is the quickest way to heal.

23:23.987 --> 23:25.697
-I don't think they say that.
-You sure?

23:25.781 --> 23:27.616
Yeah, they say something about time.

23:27.699 --> 23:29.618
Well, time to move on.

23:29.701 --> 23:30.786
I plan to

23:31.161 --> 23:33.372
while she spends
the rest of her life in a cell.

23:35.165 --> 23:37.501
Hey, about me saying that
I'm smarter than you in there...

23:37.584 --> 23:39.211
Oh, I know you think you are.

23:39.294 --> 23:40.796
That's why I always catch you.

23:41.839 --> 23:43.090
Good work.

23:43.173 --> 23:44.716
The Caracas story did the trick.

23:44.883 --> 23:47.135
-Diana got the assignment?
-And then some.

23:50.430 --> 23:51.515
Caffrey.

23:54.393 --> 23:57.688
Looks like Worth is targeting
the offices of DCFI.

23:57.771 --> 23:59.815
It's a hedge fund run by Ian Dybek.

23:59.898 --> 24:03.402
Ivy League, Upper West Sider,
golfs at clubs that don't allow women.

24:03.485 --> 24:05.237
Dybek and Worth
managed the fund together.

24:05.320 --> 24:07.155
Hmm. Until they were investigated

24:07.239 --> 24:09.032
on suspicion of market manipulation.

24:09.116 --> 24:10.409
JONES: Yeah, a bunch of strange activity

24:10.492 --> 24:13.203
from the company's server caught
the attention of the S.E.C.

24:13.287 --> 24:15.622
It turns out Worth ran
the high-frequency trading division.

24:15.706 --> 24:18.500
The S.E.C. shook him down
but didn't get enough to press charges.

24:18.584 --> 24:20.085
But Dybek fired him anyway.

24:20.794 --> 24:22.588
I think he needed a sacrificial lamb.

24:23.338 --> 24:25.382
I let Ian Dybek know

24:25.465 --> 24:28.010
that there's a security threat
on his facility.

24:28.093 --> 24:29.178
He want protection?

24:29.261 --> 24:32.806
No, he thanked me, then proceeded
to bolt out of the building.

24:33.515 --> 24:36.310
It looks like he tucked
something small in his pocket.

24:37.019 --> 24:39.479
Looks like a thumb drive.
Where was he headed?

24:39.563 --> 24:41.315
PETER: Home. I bet he had a reason.

24:41.815 --> 24:43.901
Like hiding the drive from the FBI.

24:45.110 --> 24:48.322
Firms like DCFI pay a fortune
for their trading algorithms.

24:48.405 --> 24:52.451
Yeah, a millisecond means the difference
between gaining and losing millions.

24:52.534 --> 24:54.077
If there's an algorithm on that drive,

24:54.161 --> 24:55.746
it makes sense that Worth
would want to steal it.

24:55.829 --> 24:57.164
But not why Dybek hid it.

24:57.247 --> 24:59.166
It's not illegal to use an algorithm.

25:01.126 --> 25:02.336
Unless it is.

25:03.253 --> 25:05.672
NEWSWOMAN: <i>The scene today</i>
<i>as the market plummeted 1,000 points...</i>

25:05.756 --> 25:07.007
That's a 1,000-point dead drop,

25:07.090 --> 25:09.176
all because one fund moved
a large amount of stock

25:09.259 --> 25:11.970
-when the market was vulnerable.
<i>-Indeed, the broader market...</i>

25:12.054 --> 25:15.349
It started a chain reaction
by high-frequency trading servers,

25:15.432 --> 25:17.142
which caused the market
to crash in seconds.

25:17.559 --> 25:19.144
Like high-stakes <i>Jenga.</i>

25:19.228 --> 25:22.397
Yep, but it's more like
throwing a banana peel.

25:22.481 --> 25:24.358
You're saying that
what tipped off the S.E.C.

25:24.441 --> 25:27.027
might have been Worth and Dybek
testing their algorithm

25:27.110 --> 25:29.530
to see how many ones and zeroes
they could make slip and fall.

25:29.613 --> 25:30.948
There are billions to be made.

25:31.198 --> 25:33.283
Sell short before the market dives.

25:33.367 --> 25:35.035
Be first in line when it bounces back up.

25:35.285 --> 25:38.163
The perfect crime, executed by computers.

25:38.247 --> 25:40.374
And Worth knows
if he steals the algorithm,

25:40.457 --> 25:43.710
Dybek can't report the theft
without implicating himself.

25:43.794 --> 25:46.588
If we're right, the only way to stop it
is to get that drive.

25:46.964 --> 25:48.048
We'll need a warrant.

25:48.131 --> 25:50.884
That takes time.
Worth wants the drive by Friday.

25:50.968 --> 25:52.427
What happens Friday?

25:52.511 --> 25:54.638
Uh, the new Woody Allen comes out.

25:55.722 --> 25:57.057
So does the jobs report.

25:57.307 --> 25:59.059
That means the market
is primed to be volatile.

25:59.309 --> 26:01.436
Jones, reach out to friendly
judges for that warrant.

26:01.520 --> 26:02.896
-Yep.
-I've got a briefing

26:02.980 --> 26:04.857
with the cyber division first thing.

26:04.940 --> 26:07.484
So, Diana, be ready to move on Dybek.

26:07.568 --> 26:09.486
-Take Neal.
-I have one child.

26:09.570 --> 26:10.779
Another won't be a problem.

26:10.863 --> 26:12.698
First day back, feels like old times.

26:12.781 --> 26:14.992
Play nice, you two. Play nice.

26:20.622 --> 26:23.375
-Do you remember when we first moved in?
-Mmm-hmm.

26:23.584 --> 26:25.752
We ate off a crate for three months.

26:26.753 --> 26:29.173
Let's not buy a table
for the Georgetown house.

26:29.256 --> 26:30.424
Save some money.

26:32.092 --> 26:33.260
You okay?

26:34.970 --> 26:36.180
Yeah.

26:36.263 --> 26:37.848
Yeah, we just have a lot of memories here.

26:37.931 --> 26:38.932
Mmm-hmm.

26:39.766 --> 26:41.101
We'll make some new ones.

26:42.603 --> 26:43.770
I know.

26:45.105 --> 26:46.148
Mmm.

26:46.231 --> 26:48.817
Does that have something to do
with opening a can?

26:49.193 --> 26:52.446
Mmm, no, I think it has something to do
with pitting a mango.

26:53.280 --> 26:54.573
Never used it.

26:54.698 --> 26:56.617
(CHUCKLES) Do you think Neal
would want it?

26:57.075 --> 26:58.285
I don't know,

26:58.368 --> 27:01.330
but I do know that he doesn't
want a handler anymore.

27:02.331 --> 27:06.210
Neal asked me to recommend
that his sentence be terminated.

27:06.293 --> 27:07.461
-Really?
-Yeah.

27:07.544 --> 27:08.545
-Neal?
-Yeah.

27:08.629 --> 27:09.630
Off anklet?

27:09.713 --> 27:11.089
Free to roam the world.

27:11.173 --> 27:13.383
-Imagine the trouble he'd find.
-Hmm.

27:13.634 --> 27:14.676
Or not.

27:15.052 --> 27:17.804
I don't know. Maybe Neal's changed.

27:18.305 --> 27:21.016
We have been known
to be a positive influence before.

27:21.225 --> 27:24.520
Yeah, but Rebecca not only conned him.

27:24.603 --> 27:25.938
She broke his heart.

27:27.105 --> 27:30.234
What Neal needs right now are rules,
structure.

27:31.151 --> 27:34.655
Or what he needs is to figure out
what he wants in his life.

27:35.280 --> 27:38.033
I don't know.
Maybe this was a wake-up call for Neal.

27:52.464 --> 27:54.383
Peter never makes me work this early.

27:54.466 --> 27:57.427
I've been awake since 5:00.
Sleep means nothing to a hungry baby.

27:57.511 --> 27:58.595
Drink your coffee.

27:58.679 --> 27:59.888
Where are we going?

27:59.972 --> 28:01.682
I'm undercover as Rebecca Lowe,

28:01.765 --> 28:03.350
and my assignment's
to steal that flash drive.

28:03.433 --> 28:04.560
You're gonna help me.

28:04.977 --> 28:06.103
Diana.

28:06.186 --> 28:07.479
Caffrey.

28:07.855 --> 28:09.064
We're here.

28:09.147 --> 28:11.608
Congrats on surviving
the most epic breakup ever.

28:11.692 --> 28:14.111
Oh. Thank you for not asking how I am.

28:14.194 --> 28:16.446
Two things we have in common,
hating that question...

28:16.530 --> 28:18.657
And being fine going it alone.

28:19.032 --> 28:21.118
Listen, as your C.I...

28:21.201 --> 28:23.328
-You're not my C.I.
-You're handling me.

28:23.412 --> 28:25.289
Ugh, that sounds all kinds of wrong.

28:25.372 --> 28:26.540
Well, so does this plan.

28:26.623 --> 28:28.250
Peter wants to go in with a warrant.

28:28.333 --> 28:30.627
Best case, he gets one.
Worst case, he doesn't.

28:30.711 --> 28:32.880
In which case,
we'll have the drive in hand.

28:33.547 --> 28:35.424
Motherhood's made you kind of badass.

28:35.757 --> 28:37.009
I was always a badass.

28:38.385 --> 28:39.678
NEAL: There's Dybek.

28:40.596 --> 28:42.472
That must be his wife, Iris.

28:42.556 --> 28:44.725
-DIANA: They practically are each other.
-(CELL PHONE RINGING)

28:46.602 --> 28:47.728
Karen?

28:48.228 --> 28:49.855
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Slow down.

28:50.230 --> 28:52.900
Is Theo all right? What?

28:52.983 --> 28:55.068
-What's going on?
-Okay, okay.

28:55.736 --> 28:56.987
Stay calm.

28:59.156 --> 29:01.533
Go home. I'll take it from here.

29:03.118 --> 29:04.453
Come on, I got this.

29:05.537 --> 29:06.914
Do it.

29:37.945 --> 29:39.363
Karen, I'm home.

29:39.446 --> 29:40.572
(ARGUING SOFTLY)

29:40.656 --> 29:42.282
-You!
-Shh!

29:43.992 --> 29:45.619
He said there was a gas leak.

29:45.702 --> 29:48.539
A ruse that Karen accepted
without question.

29:48.622 --> 29:50.874
You're wearing a gas company uniform.

29:50.958 --> 29:52.167
He showed me credentials.

29:52.251 --> 29:54.127
Which is more
than I can say for you, Karen,

29:54.211 --> 29:55.629
if Karen is your real name.

29:55.712 --> 29:56.797
KAREN: Do you hear this?

29:56.880 --> 29:59.800
He keeps saying my name
over and over again.

29:59.883 --> 30:01.635
(MOCKING) Karen, Karen, Karen.

30:01.718 --> 30:03.011
He refuses to leave.

30:03.220 --> 30:04.680
And he insulted my baby food.

30:05.013 --> 30:06.932
Peas are patently uninspired.

30:07.182 --> 30:10.435
Are you aware that she is a Ferberizer?

30:10.519 --> 30:12.813
-Ferberizer?
-That's it. I quit.

30:13.605 --> 30:14.940
-I can't take this.
-(SCOFFS)

30:15.023 --> 30:16.859
No, Karen. No, no.
Please, I'm begging you.

30:16.942 --> 30:18.110
I'm sorry, Diana.

30:18.819 --> 30:19.945
(DIANA SIGHS)

30:21.488 --> 30:24.366
Do you have any idea
how long it took me to find that nanny?

30:24.449 --> 30:25.450
Oh, please.

30:25.534 --> 30:28.245
She was one step away
from Louis Wain cat drawings.

30:28.328 --> 30:30.205
Mozzie, how can you do this to me?

30:30.289 --> 30:31.707
The real question is,

30:31.790 --> 30:35.544
how could you let this baby
sit in a wood-paneled nursery?

30:35.627 --> 30:37.504
A black and white chevron pattern

30:37.588 --> 30:40.507
would be much more stimulating
to his burgeoning neurons.

30:40.591 --> 30:42.968
Here's the part where
I arrest you for home invasion.

30:43.051 --> 30:44.219
That hurts.

30:44.386 --> 30:49.057
You know, it's not too late
to build a small geodesic dome in here.

30:49.141 --> 30:50.851
It will really aid in his spatial skills.

30:50.934 --> 30:52.686
When would I build a dome?

30:52.769 --> 30:55.647
I'm a working mother
with no child care now thanks to you.

30:55.814 --> 30:57.566
(BABY COOING)

30:57.649 --> 30:58.901
He likes you.

30:58.984 --> 31:01.111
Of course he does.

31:01.195 --> 31:03.071
I literally pulled him with these...

31:03.155 --> 31:04.656
We do not need to relive that.

31:05.407 --> 31:07.534
All right, he's yours for the day.

31:08.535 --> 31:11.580
If he gets fussy, that mobile my mother
bought him calms him down.

31:11.663 --> 31:12.998
Nap time?

31:13.081 --> 31:15.918
-Every three hours.
-Okay, Teddy.

31:16.001 --> 31:17.294
It's Theo.

31:18.754 --> 31:20.088
(SPEAKING GIBBERISH)

31:43.487 --> 31:44.780
(DOOR OPENING)

31:45.030 --> 31:46.573
WOMAN: Ian!

31:57.626 --> 32:00.212
(IN SING-SONG) Love bun?

32:02.214 --> 32:05.592
Bunny, where are you?

32:06.218 --> 32:07.386
(EXCLAIMS)

32:08.136 --> 32:10.722
I'm wearing your favorite outfit.

32:28.031 --> 32:32.077
Ian, my love bunny.

32:32.160 --> 32:33.620
I'm coming.

32:34.413 --> 32:36.123
Bunny?

32:36.290 --> 32:37.791
-(SCREAMING)
-Oh!

32:39.585 --> 32:40.752
Oh, God.

32:46.758 --> 32:47.926
-(SCREAMS)
-Hey!

32:48.135 --> 32:51.388
-I am not afraid to use this.
-I did not mean to scare you.

32:51.471 --> 32:52.931
Wow. I think I know what happened.

32:53.015 --> 32:55.267
-I think we were double-booked.
-What?

32:55.350 --> 32:56.768
I'm here for Iris.

32:56.852 --> 32:59.730
You know, we spend time together
while her husband's at work.

33:00.564 --> 33:02.482
Oh. Oh!

33:02.608 --> 33:04.026
You mean Iris has a...

33:04.109 --> 33:08.030
Mister, although that is a very coarse
word to describe what she and I have.

33:08.113 --> 33:09.114
Oh, I know, right?

33:09.198 --> 33:10.365
Right.

33:11.241 --> 33:12.492
IAN: Fluffer-nutter?

33:13.785 --> 33:16.288
All right, just hold him off
until I can get out of here.

33:16.371 --> 33:18.540
I'll call Iris and suggest a hotel.

33:18.624 --> 33:20.042
Your secret's safe with me.

33:21.001 --> 33:22.336
We both have so much in common,

33:22.419 --> 33:24.296
-beyond looking great in silk.
-Thank you.

33:30.052 --> 33:31.345
Fluffer-nutter?

33:33.305 --> 33:35.265
Ian? Bunny?

33:35.682 --> 33:36.808
Ian, hi.

33:36.892 --> 33:38.227
I got a meeting in 10 minutes.

33:38.310 --> 33:39.978
Oh, but I want a change of pace.

33:40.062 --> 33:41.396
I want a change of scenery.

33:41.480 --> 33:43.732
On the couch, please? Please?

33:43.815 --> 33:46.985
Oh! I just want you.
I want you so bad. Right now!

33:49.821 --> 33:50.906
(GIGGLES)

33:51.740 --> 33:52.991
Oh! Eyes on me.

33:53.075 --> 33:55.077
Do not look away.

34:04.044 --> 34:05.712
Neal broke into Dybek's residence,

34:05.796 --> 34:07.589
cracked his safe and stole this

34:07.673 --> 34:10.467
with no proof that the man is anything
but the target of a heist,

34:10.551 --> 34:12.052
-and you sanctioned it.
-Correct.

34:12.761 --> 34:14.513
I told you to wait
until we have a warrant.

34:14.596 --> 34:15.639
Did you get one?

34:15.722 --> 34:16.974
Not yet, but that doesn't mean...

34:17.057 --> 34:18.308
By tomorrow morning?

34:18.976 --> 34:22.271
Look, if the algorithm's on that drive,
I couldn't risk Dybek using it.

34:22.354 --> 34:24.064
You put me in charge. I made a call.

34:24.147 --> 34:25.732
You've let Neal cross lines for years.

34:26.108 --> 34:28.569
Diana, trust me. Do as I say.

34:29.278 --> 34:31.572
Actions make us who we are.
I stand by mine.

34:34.074 --> 34:35.367
Guys,

34:35.450 --> 34:36.910
I confirmed what's on the drive.

34:42.499 --> 34:45.586
Hmm. Now we know what
an algorithm looks like.

34:45.669 --> 34:47.671
Right. Just a complicated
series of commands

34:47.754 --> 34:50.340
to buy and sell, but when I applied it

34:50.424 --> 34:52.843
to a simulation of the major
stock market indexes,

34:52.926 --> 34:54.469
the market goes into a nosedive.

34:54.761 --> 34:55.762
(WHISTLES)

34:57.347 --> 35:00.767
Irreversible
with catastrophic consequences.

35:00.851 --> 35:03.520
In eight hours, our economy
would've been in chaos.

35:03.604 --> 35:05.981
And Worth would've been
richer than Scrooge McDuck.

35:06.064 --> 35:07.858
Wall Street's a game.

35:07.941 --> 35:09.860
He's got all the pieces in place,

35:09.943 --> 35:13.197
the algorithm, the capital
and the jobs report.

35:13.280 --> 35:14.698
And he won't stop till he pulls it off.

35:14.781 --> 35:16.158
Then I say we let him win.

35:16.241 --> 35:18.368
If it's a game, we can all play.

35:18.452 --> 35:20.746
-He just won't know it.
-Exactly.

35:20.829 --> 35:22.372
Jones, contact the tech team.

35:22.456 --> 35:24.917
We've got until the market opens.

35:31.089 --> 35:32.841
-(ECHOING) Test.
-Yep, you're live.

35:33.383 --> 35:35.219
-You got me?
-Yeah.

35:35.302 --> 35:37.346
So that's identical
to the one in Dybek's safe?

35:37.429 --> 35:38.722
On the outside.

35:38.805 --> 35:41.517
On the inside,
it's a high-bandwidth Wi-Fi receiver.

35:41.600 --> 35:44.394
Once Worth plugs it in,
we'll control his computer.

35:44.478 --> 35:46.438
He'll apply the algorithm,
and if it works...

35:46.522 --> 35:48.023
He'll be fooled into thinking
the market's tanking.

35:48.106 --> 35:49.149
Bingo.

35:49.233 --> 35:51.818
And when he uses his firm's clients' money
to make his trades,

35:51.902 --> 35:55.113
we got him on wire fraud,
conspiracy, money laundering...

35:55.239 --> 35:57.407
Intention to disrupt the U.S. economy.

35:57.491 --> 36:01.203
And hiring an international thief/assassin
to do his bidding.

36:04.081 --> 36:06.792
Ah! Bring it to me.

36:08.168 --> 36:09.753
You get the drive when I get my money.

36:09.837 --> 36:11.046
And you'll receive payment

36:11.129 --> 36:14.007
when I know that those aren't
Ian's snapshots from Augusta.

36:23.016 --> 36:25.185
-We're in?
-We're in.

36:28.272 --> 36:29.690
There she is.

36:31.233 --> 36:32.359
And...

36:34.570 --> 36:36.029
There she goes.

36:37.447 --> 36:39.324
Is that what's supposed to happen?

36:39.408 --> 36:42.619
It's a little difficult
to explain to someone like you.

36:43.203 --> 36:44.580
(CELL PHONE CHIMING)

36:47.958 --> 36:49.960
I could explain it to you.

36:50.377 --> 36:52.754
Keep it simple so I understand.

36:54.298 --> 36:55.757
I just made a killing.

36:56.884 --> 36:58.010
Your turn.

36:58.844 --> 36:59.970
Explain that.

37:07.603 --> 37:08.854
Or I could tell you

37:08.937 --> 37:11.231
what happened to the last guy
who pointed a gun at me.

37:11.315 --> 37:13.108
-Her cover's blown.
-Let's move.

37:13.942 --> 37:15.068
Who the hell are you?

37:15.485 --> 37:16.820
I'm Rebecca Lowe.

37:17.529 --> 37:18.697
Who referred me?

37:19.031 --> 37:22.242
-An associate from Zurich.
-I'm not a fed.

37:22.326 --> 37:24.119
Yeah, that's not a bet
that I care to hedge.

37:24.244 --> 37:25.287
Do you really think the government

37:25.370 --> 37:27.664
would let millions of people
lose billions of dollars

37:27.748 --> 37:28.999
to sting one man?

37:29.249 --> 37:30.375
You're not that special.

37:30.459 --> 37:32.794
Now give me my money. We're done.

37:43.639 --> 37:45.265
Have you ever held a gun before?

37:47.059 --> 37:48.352
FBI.

37:48.894 --> 37:50.354
You're under arrest.

37:50.938 --> 37:52.272
Hands behind your back.

37:52.564 --> 37:53.607
Now!

37:58.362 --> 37:59.571
You okay?

38:01.698 --> 38:02.950
Of course you are.

38:03.534 --> 38:04.868
Let's go.

38:07.538 --> 38:08.956
Who the hell sent that text?

38:16.964 --> 38:18.131
What do we have?

38:18.215 --> 38:20.300
Tracing the SIM card
from Worth's phone now.

38:20.676 --> 38:23.220
Peter, you won't believe where
that text message came from.

38:23.303 --> 38:24.596
Where?

38:24.888 --> 38:27.641
-The Metropolitan Corrections Center.
-Rebecca.

38:36.942 --> 38:39.111
Warden Maxwell,
how the hell did she gain access

38:39.194 --> 38:40.362
to a cell phone?

38:40.445 --> 38:42.906
One of my best agents
was put in harm's way.

38:43.448 --> 38:46.159
You and me, we're gonna get
to the bottom of this.

38:46.702 --> 38:49.413
Peter, cell phones are currency in prison.
It happens.

38:49.496 --> 38:51.123
Not with cop killers it doesn't.

38:52.082 --> 38:53.917
-If anything had...
-Well, it didn't.

38:54.001 --> 38:55.502
We're not going there.

39:00.549 --> 39:02.092
What do you say we both go home?

39:07.181 --> 39:11.685
See, they want you to think
the <i>Apollo</i> landed on the moon.

39:11.768 --> 39:13.103
What they don't want you to know

39:13.187 --> 39:17.566
is that the "spaceship" landed
in our own backyard six times.

39:18.317 --> 39:19.693
(GURGLING)

39:22.821 --> 39:24.239
Come on.

39:24.948 --> 39:27.784
What's more interesting
than a good lunar con?

39:40.631 --> 39:43.634
Kid, you're kidding me!

39:46.220 --> 39:47.471
Of course.

39:47.554 --> 39:51.225
Every symbol could represent a number.

39:51.767 --> 39:54.269
Mosconi's symbols aren't a message.

39:54.770 --> 39:56.230
They're numbers.

39:57.272 --> 39:59.775
Numbers we understand.

40:00.609 --> 40:01.985
Numbers we can work with.

40:02.069 --> 40:04.279
Don't let anyone tell you
you'll never use math.

40:05.113 --> 40:06.365
Wow.

40:06.823 --> 40:08.492
You're really good with babies.

40:08.575 --> 40:09.993
Oh. Hairline.

40:10.911 --> 40:12.621
And your timing is impeccable.

40:18.460 --> 40:20.671
PETER: We have Dybek in custody.

40:20.754 --> 40:23.173
And just like any criminal,
he lawyered up.

40:24.258 --> 40:26.134
I wouldn't expect any less.

40:31.181 --> 40:35.853
All these times, I not only allowed
but encouraged you to break the rules...

40:35.978 --> 40:37.229
Hell, the law.

40:37.312 --> 40:38.730
It was never lost on me

40:38.814 --> 40:41.316
that the actions I took
were sanctioned by the FBI.

40:41.400 --> 40:43.944
I was focused on closing cases.

40:44.027 --> 40:45.737
And I let you scratch an itch.

40:45.821 --> 40:47.990
I have a great dermatologist.

40:49.116 --> 40:50.701
Actions define us.

40:51.285 --> 40:52.786
I made sure yours did.

40:54.162 --> 40:56.623
Got one question for you, just one.

40:57.958 --> 40:59.293
Shoot.

41:00.419 --> 41:02.212
Do you think you can go straight?

41:05.007 --> 41:06.300
Yes.

41:06.550 --> 41:09.428
Peter, I've never lied to you.

41:09.511 --> 41:12.389
Neal, you've double-talked,
omitted and bent the truth.

41:12.472 --> 41:14.892
One word. No loopholes.

41:16.643 --> 41:17.686
Yes.

41:17.895 --> 41:19.062
(SIGHS)

41:19.146 --> 41:20.772
I want to believe it.

41:20.856 --> 41:23.108
But after all you've done,
I'm not sure I can.

41:25.110 --> 41:26.695
If you can't...

41:28.864 --> 41:30.657
I'll have to do it on my own.

41:31.867 --> 41:34.203
(PHONES RINGING)

41:38.999 --> 41:41.001
WOMAN: I'll get it.
MAN: FBI.

41:42.836 --> 41:44.171
(CELL PHONE BUZZING)

41:44.796 --> 41:46.381
This is Agent Burke.

41:50.052 --> 41:51.303
How?

41:51.386 --> 41:52.596
What?

41:53.680 --> 41:54.765
Peter, what is it?

41:54.848 --> 41:56.350
Rebecca escaped.

41:57.768 --> 41:59.061
Neal?

41:59.686 --> 42:01.063
Neal?

42:01.563 --> 42:03.023
Seriously?

42:06.527 --> 42:08.195
<i>This is Neal. Leave a message.</i>

42:08.278 --> 42:09.655
Neal, where are you?

42:09.738 --> 42:11.865
It's 4:00 a.m.
I've been calling all night.

42:11.949 --> 42:13.534
I have glorious news.

42:14.076 --> 42:16.495
Thanks to baby Teddy, I'll explain later,

42:16.578 --> 42:20.040
we know that Mosconi's
last clues were numbers.

42:20.123 --> 42:22.042
Numbers that, by the time you get home,

42:22.125 --> 42:24.086
will lead us to the diamond.
